## 39. PROTOCOL INTEGRITY & POST-EDIT AUDIT MANDATE (v3.38.25)
- **PRINCIPLE**: The protocol files (`.cursorrules`, `CLAUDE.md`, `.agents/gemini.md`) are the agent's core identity. Their integrity is non-negotiable.
- **ANTI-DELETION LOCK**: Using `multi_replace_file_content` to replace or remove entire numbered sections of these files is STRICTLY PROHIBITED unless explicitly requested for a refactor.
- **MANDATORY VISUAL AUDIT**: After ANY automated edit to a protocol file, the agent MUST perform a `view_file` call on the affected lines (including 10 lines of surrounding context) to verify that no sections were accidentally wiped out.
- **NO SILENT REMOVAL**: If a section is intended for removal (e.g., duplicates), the agent MUST explicitly state this in the tool description and verify the deletion is successful without affecting other sections.

40. NETWORK-ADDRESS ISOLATION & PURGE MANDATE (v3.40.7)
- **ANTI-BLIND-PURGE**: PERFORMING GLOBAL SEARCH-AND-REPLACE ON CONTRACT ADDRESSES IS STRICTLY PROHIBITED. Every address shift (e.g., V13.1 -> V13.2) MUST be performed file-by-file with explicit context verification (Mainnet vs Sepolia vs Test).
- **MAINNET PLACEHOLDER INTEGRITY**: Mainnet addresses (e.g., `VITE_V12_CONTRACT_ADDRESS`) MUST remain `[RESERVED]` or their verified legacy value (V12) until a literal deployment to Mainnet is confirmed via transaction hash. NEVER assume Sepolia addresses (`0xaC43...`) apply to Mainnet endpoints.
- **LOGICAL NETWORK BOUNDARY**: Verification scripts (e.g., `check-logs.js`, `verify_deploy_status.cjs`) MUST maintain separate arrays or clear labels for Mainnet and Sepolia. PROHIBIT "blind" population of Mainnet-labeled arrays with testnet data.
- **CROSS-REFERENCE ENFORCEMENT**: Before updating any address in documentation, SKILL, or script, and Agent MUST verify the value against BOTH `.env` and `.agents/WORKSPACE_MAP.md`.
- **40.5 RPC TRUTHINESS MANDATE (v3.40.9)**: DILARANG KERAS menggunakan perbandingan naif `code !== '0x'` atau `code != '0x'`. Akibat sifat JavaScript, `undefined` atau `null` akan lolos sebagai "True" (False Positive). WAJIB menggunakan: `code && code !== '0x' && code !== '0x0'`.
- **40.6 DIRECT EVIDENCE MANDATE**: Laporan status "DEPLOYED" tidak sah tanpa bukti literal. Setiap skrip verifikasi atau laporan chat WAJIB menyertakan **10 karakter pertama bytecode** (contoh: `0x608060...`) untuk membuktikan eksistensi kontrak secara fisik, bukan hanya tanda centang (✅).
- **40.7 ZERO-ASSUMPTION SHIFT**: Jika skrip verifikasi memberikan hasil yang tidak terduga (misal Sepolia addr muncul di Mainnet), Agent DILARANG melanjutkan narasi. Agent WAJIB segera melakukan **Raw Debug Dump** (seperti `debug-getcode.js`) dan cross-check via block explorer sebelum memberikan interpretasi kepada User.

- **40.8 SPECIALIZED ENV AUDIT MANDATE (v3.40.11)**: THE `sync` COMMAND (and `/sync-contracts-audit` workflow) MUST explicitly audit and synchronize the following 6 specialized environment files:
  - `.env.example`, `.env.local`, `.env.vercel`, `.env.vercel.preview`, `.env.vercel.production`, `.env.verification.vercel`.
  - **MANDATE**: Every sync execution MUST verify that legacy addresses (0xfA75, 0xDe61, 0x87a3) are purged and replaced with the canonical v3.40.11 verified SOT addresses (`0xaC43...`).

- **41.0 GLOBAL MOBILE UI HARDENING (v3.40.18)**: Every UI update MUST adhere to "Native+" standards.
  - **MANDATE**: Enforce 11px micro-typography and notch-proof safe areas across all mobile viewports.
  - **VERIFICATION**: UI audits MUST be performed via browser sub-agent on multiple device emulations (iPhone SE, Pro Max).

- **41.2 ANTI-WHALE XP SCALING (v3.41.2)**: 🚨 PROHIBIT manual scaling or multiplier calculations in the backend (`api/`) or frontend (`src/`).
  - **MANDATE**: All XP increments MUST be processed via the Supabase RPC `fn_increment_xp(p_wallet, p_amount)`.
  - **TRUTH**: The logarithmic Global Multiplier and Tier-Safe Individual Multiplier are purely database-side logic. Agents MUST send raw `Base_XP` from `point_settings` to the RPC.

- **42.0 REFERRAL GROWTH LOOP v2 (v3.42.0)**: 🚨 MANDATORY VESTING & DIVIDENDS.
  - **MANDATE**: Referral bonuses (50 XP) MUST ONLY be awarded after the referred user reaches the **500 XP threshold**.
  - **PASSIVE INCOME**: Tier 1 referrers MUST receive a **10% lifetime XP dividend** from their invites, handled atomically via `fn_increment_xp`.
  - **LOGGING**: Every referral dividend MUST generate a `REFERRAL_DIVIDEND` log entry in `user_activity_logs`.

- **42.1 BASE SOCIAL IDENTITY GUARD (v3.42.0)**: 🚨 IDENTITY-LOCKED TASKS.
  - **MANDATE**: High-value tasks MUST be gated behind `is_base_social_verified`. 
  - **VERIFICATION**: Basename reverse resolution is the standard for identity proof. Admin tasks MUST enforce `is_base_social_required` labels.

- **42.2 DISAPPEARING TASK MANDATE (v3.42.2)**: 🚨 CLEAN SWEEP INTERFACE.
  - **MANDATE**: Tasks and mission cards MUST be hidden immediately upon completion/claim. 
  - **IMPLEMENTATION**: Use `return null` or array filtering in `TasksPage.jsx` based on `hasCompletedTask` or `hasClaimed`.
  - **SPONSORSHIP**: Gated mission cards MUST vanish if all child tasks are complete.
  - **EMPTY STATE**: Display the "YOU ARE ALL CAUGHT UP!" banner as a positive reinforcement.

- **UI/UX**: Linkage status MUST be clearly differentiated between "Verified" (Premium Shield) and "Unverified" (Call-to-Action).

- **42.4 TASK FEATURE INTEGRITY HARDENING (v3.42.8)**: 🚨 NATIVE+ & METADATA CONSISTENCY.
  - **MANDATE**: All primary action buttons (Daily Tasks, Partner Offers, Buy Ticket) MUST use `bg-indigo-600/20`, `border-indigo-500/30`, and `text-indigo-400` with NO decorative icons.
  - **LAYOUT**: Root wrappers MUST implement `overflow-x-hidden` and `max-w-[100vw]` to prevent horizontal clipping.
  - **TYPE-SAFETY**: Task filtering in `TaskList.jsx` and similar components MUST use `String()` conversion for comparing Contract IDs (Integer) and Supabase (UUID).
  - **REACTIVE SYNC**: UI logic MUST explicitly handle `already_claimed: true` success flag to resolve state race conditions and show accurate mission completion status.
  - **PIPELINE INTEGRITY**: Task creation/sync in `admin-bundle.js` MUST include `title`, `expires_at`, `target_id`, and `min_neynar_score`. Task cleanup MUST be performed periodically to maintain a healthy baseline.

