### SECTION 51: TASK FEATURE INTEGRITY MANDATE (v3.51.2) 🎯

> **CANONICAL REFERENCE**: `PRD/TASK_FEATURE_WORKFLOW.md`
> This document is the ABSOLUTE Source of Truth for all Task feature logic.
> Agents MUST read it BEFORE modifying ANY of the following files:
> - `src/pages/TasksPage.jsx` (On-Chain Tasks UI)
> - `src/components/tasks/TaskList.jsx` (Off-Chain Tasks UI)
> - `src/components/tasks/OffersList.jsx` (Partner Campaigns)
> - `src/hooks/useVerification.js` (Social Verify Flow)
> - `src/hooks/useVerifiedAction.js` (Secure Claim Flow)
> - `src/hooks/useContract.js` (On-Chain Read/Write)
> - `src/dailyAppLogic.js` (XP Award Bridge)
> - `api/tasks-bundle.js` (Backend Task Handlers)
> - `src/lib/contracts.js` (ABI & Address Config)
> - `src/lib/economy.js` (Hybrid Formula Mirror)

**31.1 DUAL TASK PIPELINE AWARENESS**:
- On-Chain Tasks: Read from `DailyApp V13.2` contract → verify via `useVerification` → claim via `tasks-bundle.js handleSocialVerify`.
- Off-Chain Tasks: Read from `daily_tasks` table → claim via `useVerifiedAction` → `tasks-bundle.js handleClaim`.
- Both pipelines MUST terminate at `fn_increment_xp()` in Postgres. NEVER calculate XP scaling in JS.

**31.2 XP RESOLUTION PRIORITY**:
1. `point_settings` dynamic key (`{platform}_{action_type}`)
2. Fallback: `daily_tasks.xp_reward`
3. All scaling: `fn_increment_xp` (Hybrid Formula: G × I × U, Floor=5)

**31.3 ANTI-SYBIL & METADATA ENFORCEMENT**:
- `target_id` uniqueness per claim (FID/TweetID link)
- `expires_at` mandatory for campaigns/sponsored tasks
- `min_neynar_score` gating for Farcaster reputation
- UNIQUE(wallet_address, task_id) constraint
- EIP-191 signature on every write operation
- 30s anti-fraud delay before social verify

**31.4 DISAPPEARING TASK ENFORCEMENT** (reiterated from Section 42.2):
- Completed tasks: `return null` (NOT badge "DONE")
- Type-safe comparison: `String(c.task_id) === String(task.id)`
- Reactive sync on `already_claimed` flag or "already completed" error

## 43. ECOSYSTEM SECURITY REMEDIATION MANDATE (v3.43.0)
- **Clean-Pipe Sync Protocol**: DILARANG KERAS melakukan verifikasi environment tanpa menggunakan skrip `robust_sync.cjs` atau yang setara (spawnSync + stdin).
- **Multi-Project Parity**: Setiap perubahan pada environment di satu proyek Vercel (Frontend) wajib disinkronkan ke proyek pendukung (Verification Server) secara atomis menggunakan mandate Multi-Vercel Sync.
- **Zero-Trust Token Rotation**: VERCEL_TOKEN wajib dianggap sebagai materi berisiko tinggi; setiap indikasi kebocoran harus memicu rotasi total dan audit sinkronisasi ulang.
- **Audit-First Deployment**: DILARANG melakukan `vercel --prod` tanpa menjalankan audit `check_sync_status.cjs` terlebih dahulu.

## 44. MEDIA PRIVACY & ZERO-SNAPSHOT MANDATE (CTO MANDATE v3.43.1)
- **PRINCIPLE**: Data visual yang diambil dari browser seringkali mengandung informasi sensitif (PII, tokens, private UI).
- **STORAGE POLICY**:
  - Media (JPG, PNG, WEBP, MP4) **TIDAK BOLEH** disimpan di cloud, direktori publik, atau masuk ke dalam Git history.
  - Aset aplikasi resmi (Logo, Icon, UI assets) diperbolehkan di lokal saja selama tidak mengandung data sensitif.
- **AUTO-PURGE MANDATE**: Setiap kali Agent menyelesaikan tugas yang melibatkan `browser_subagent`, Agent WAJIB menjalankan perintah penghapusan cache internal secara rekursif pada direktori `browser_recordings/` dan `**/browser/`.
- **DATA SOVEREIGNTY**: Tanggung jawab keamanan data sensitif berada pada Agent sebagai perpanjangan tangan CTO/Owner. Kegagalan menghapus snapshot adalah pelanggaran berat terhadap Zero-Leak Protocol.

## 45. DESIGN PROTOCOL & AGENTIC VISUAL IDENTITY (v3.44.0)
- **DESIGN SOURCE OF TRUTH**: `DESIGN.md` is the ABSOLUTE authority on colors, typography, and component rationale.
- **MANDATE**: Agents MUST read `DESIGN.md` and use the `.agents/skills/design-protocol/SKILL.md` before initiating any frontend changes.
- **AUDIT**: Run `node scripts/audits/design_lint.cjs` before every frontend PR to ensure token integrity.
- **AESTHETIC**: Enforce "Midnight Cyber" (Dark #050505, Glassmorphism, 11px/13px balanced typography).

## 46. SDK-FIRST SWAP ENGINE (v3.47.0)
- **BUILD STABILITY**: NEVER use `@lifi/widget` or massive monolithic UI libraries that crash Rollup AST parsers during production builds on Vercel.
- **MANDATE**: Always implement custom, lightweight swap interfaces using `@lifi/sdk` directly to maintain "Native+" aesthetics and build integrity.

